  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the end of the garden was, was Copenhagen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was very close into the city.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was president of a electric manufacturing company, like a very small G for Denmark.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he is from a family of engineers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His father was, was an engineer, and, and president of the-- the what, what is the MIT of Denmark.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And his brothers were all engineers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he actually had been in this country to get further training and was called back to, to this directorship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived a comfortable life, without being extravagant in many ways.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family was very assimilated, and I did not know I was Jewish until 1943, when we had to hide and, and flee in the country.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not celebrate any Jewish holidays, and I had, had no knowledge of it at all.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the war, I know that he, he would go on Rosh-- on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And actually he had inherited from his father a seat in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I believe my grandfather also would go every year on, on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, but I didn't know about that before the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I do know that after the war, he would try to go if he was in the country at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all I remember is seeing the planes come and dropping leaflets to say that, that, that they were friendly planes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And life pretty much continued for us children uninterrupted.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And slowly, as the confrontation started with, with the, the people who were, were working against the Germans, young people like us also would demonstrate some defiance by wearing the Royal Air Force colors and things like that.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
